<https://schema.acdd.dev/v1.3/geospatial_lat_max> <http://purl.org/dc/terms/source> <https://wiki.esipfed.org/Attribute_Convention_for_Data_Discovery_1-3#geospatial_lat_max> .
<https://schema.acdd.dev/v1.3/geospatial_lat_max> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#comment> "Describes a simple upper latitude limit; may be part of a 2- or 3-dimensional bounding region. Geospatial_lat_max specifies the northernmost latitude covered by the dataset."@en .
<https://schema.acdd.dev/v1.3/geospatial_lat_max> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "geospatial_lat_max"@en .
