<https://schema.acdd.dev/v1.3/source> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#comment> "The method of production of the original data. If it was model-generated, source should name the model and its version. If it is observational, source should characterize it. This attribute is defined in the CF Conventions. Examples: 'temperature from CTD #1234'; 'world model v.0.1'."@en .
